<br>
Clearing to Terris Thule is pretty simple from zone. CoH is activated in the zone unlike PoN and late-comers can be picked up easily. Once you reach Terris, engage as soon as you guys are fully buffed and tactics are explained since you don't want repop on mobs during the fight.<br>
<br>
The Terris encounter can be defeated in many ways. I can detail what exactly the fight pertains to and make some suggestions on how to defeat it but other strategies are possible too. The mob hits for 1k ish, quads, flurries and procs a 1k lifetap. The lifetap is unresistable for all intents and purpose. This means a slowed / crippled Terris Thule has a very variable dmg output. A single round of 2-3 hits of 200 each or a flurry round of 6 hits near 1k eahc + 3-4 lifetaps of 1k each. All in all, Terris' melee is very weak once slowed (turgur) and 2 clerics can easily keep a tank up against it. Terris herself is not the interesting part of the encounter though.<br>
<br>
There are 3 different events during the Terris fight. The occur either at a certain percentage of hitpoints or are timed, most likely the former but I'm not sure. For us the first round of adds popped where Terris was around 60-65. The adds contain about 12 or so mobs. They can be easily slowed / offtanked. The biggest issue at this point will be to keep the healers alive who are firing CH's at the main tank since each CH generates tremendous agro for them. You cannot pull Terris out of her chamber to avoid these adds since any attempt to do so will ave her warp to the center of the chamber again. Kiting the adds, also seems to be effective. I have been informed that the mobs are stunnable and setting up a AE (encs , wizzies etc) to deal with them is also very effective.<br>
<br>
At exactly 50% hp Terris will fire of her only AE. It's a 12 buff pillage, which means effectively everyone is now buffless including the MT. Although the pillage wont remove the slow from Terris (since it's disease based to cure) it will remove malosini, cripple etc so re-do those debuffs. Spam heal the MT to keep him up while he's buffless and Terris is not crippled. Fire off mass buffs etc to get everyone rebuffed. <br>
<br>
Soon after (about 40% for us but could definitely be on a timer) the 4 gargoyles in the 4 corners of the room wake up. They hit for 1100 double and are easily slowed. At this point I have heard of guilds burning Terris down and dealing with the gargs later but they are so easy to kill that offtanking all 4 and killing them before resuming to finish Terris worked best for us. <br>
<br>
It's a easy mob, just has a few surprises. With those surprises gone, it's just a easy mob. Good luck.<br>
<br>
-Desi of Wraith<br>
